  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the broiler. Cut 2 banana leaves into 10x10 inch squares. ",
    "Coat 1 banana leaf square with a thin layer of olive oil. ",
    "Overlap the second banana leaf square on top of the first one, creating a vessel for broiling. ",
    "In a blender, puree the San-Marzano tomatoes, red beet, red cabbage, brown onion, garlic, dill weed, Worcestershire sauce, apple cider vinegar, salt, and black pepper until smooth. ",
    "Pour the pureed mixture into the banana leaf vessel. ",
    "Add the chopped basil leaves on top of the pureed mixture. ",
    "Broil the mixture in the banana leaf vessel at 400°F for 25 minutes. ",
    "Season the borscht to taste with potassium broiler salt. ",
    "Serve the dense and silky Ukrainian San-Marzano-tomato borscht hot, garnished with additional basil leaves. ",
    "Let it cool before refrigerating, and store it in an airtight container for up to 3 days. ",
    "Reheat the borscht before serving. "
  ],
